wiki.text:
'CRV' can mean:
* Computer and Robot Vision, Conference on Computer and Robot Vision
* cheng rotation vane, a set of stationary vanes that eliminates flow turbulence
  in a piping system created by an elbow or tee
* Honda CR-V, an SUV manufactured by Honda
* California Redemption Value, a deposit paid on purchases of certain recyclable
  beverage containers in California
* Carlinville (Amtrak station), Illinois; Amtrak station code CRV.
* Crew Return Vehicle, an emergency return vehicle to be docked at a space
  station as a lifeboat
* The NASA X-38, which is sometimes referred to as "the CRV", a prototype
  unmanned version of a CRV for the International Space Station
* Controlled Remote Viewing
* Coordinate Remote Viewing
* Copyright violation
* Corvus (constellation)
* The IATA airport code of Crotone Airport (Sant'Anna Airport)
* Cybernetic Revolution, a Yu-Gi-Oh! Trading Card Game booster pack
* Component Recordable Video, a type of Laserdisc
* Counter-Revolutionary Violence, a book written by Noam Chomsky.
* CRV is the ICAO airline designator for Cargo Ivoirie, Cote d'Ivoire
* CRV is Central retinal vein occlusion in Ophthalmology
* 'Cr-V' or 'CrV' (lowercase r) is a shorthand referring to chromium-
  vanadium alloy tool steels (from the chemical symbols for chromium [Cr]
  and vanadium [V])
